  faq={[
    { q: 'What is async/await in JavaScript?', a: 'async/await is syntax that lets you write promise-based asynchronous code as if it were synchronous. Marking a function async makes it return a promise, and await pauses inside that function until a promise settles, so you read the logic top to bottom instead of chaining .then calls.' },
    { q: 'Is async/await better than promises?', a: "They're the same thing underneath - async/await is built on promises and just reads more clearly for sequential steps and try/catch error handling. Promise combinators like Promise.all are still the right tool for running work in parallel, so you mix both." },
